HEADWORD: Subaqueous
<hw>Sub*a"que*ous</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Being under water,
or beneath the surface of water; adapted for use under water; submarine;
<as>as, a <ex>subaqueous</ex> helmet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Formed in or under water; <as>as,
<ex>subaqueous</ex> deposits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subarachnoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
